Given these findings, the most likely clinical finding observed in this patient on an echocardiogram would be a left ventricular ejection fraction (LVEF) of 41%, which is below the normal range of 55-70%. This would indicate that the patient has systolic heart failure, which is characterized by a reduced ability of the left ventricle to pump blood effectively.

